// capsules/sfn/test/src/child_diag.sfn — Child-process failure diagnostics
// (SFN-87 / #1726).
//
// E2e tests that spawn a nested `sfn run`/`build`/`check`/`emit` via
// `process.run_capture` and assert `exit == 0` tend to discard the child's
// captured stdout/stderr. When the child fails, the only surviving output
// is `assertion failed` — the real error (OOM, SIGABRT, a genuine emit
// bug) is lost, which is why the macOS-nightly roaming e2e flake has never
// been root-caused. `report_child_failure` is the one reusable helper that
// surfaces both streams on failure instead.
//
// `report_child_failure` is `![io]` (it prints) and therefore cannot be
// built from the `expect_*` matchers in this capsule, which are `![pure]`.
fn report_child_failure(tag: string, exit: int, out: string, err: string) ![io] {
    if exit == 0 { return; }
    print.err("[" + tag + "] child failed exit=" + number_to_string(exit)
        + " stdout:\n"
        + out
        + "\nstderr:\n"
        + err);
}
